    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Eumerus lyneborgi sp. nov., metatarsus. A: male, holotype, scale bar = 0.25mm; B: female, paratype (Namibia), scale bar = 0.5 mm. Legend: e, spur-like expansion." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4306507/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306523>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Eumerus vestitus, females, paralectotypes, metatibiae.A: specimen with typical E. vestitus morphology; B: outlier specimen (non-conspecific?). Scale bar = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4306523/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4306519>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Eumerus vestitus, male, lectotype, body, overall appearance. A: dorsal view with original labels; B: lateral view. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
